User now asks: Chat history summary: can you provide me with workshops that can help manage stress Absolutely, I'm glad you're looking for resources to help manage stress. One workshop that could be beneficial for you is the "Stress Better: Skills for Managing Stress" workshop hosted by the Craft Center and CAPS. This workshop takes place on Thursdays from 2-3pm, starting from Week 1 to Week 10. You'll have the opportunity to learn effective techniques for dealing with stress or mild anxiety, and you'll explore two usable strategies each week with Melissa Hawthorne-Campos, LCSW. The location is at the Craft Center in Sixth College, so it's a great way to engage in self-care and relaxation in a creative environment.

If you're interested in improving your sleep to further manage stress, you might also want to look into the "Sleep Reset" program. Proper sleep is crucial for overall well-being and can have a significant impact on stress levels. 

I hope these resources are helpful for you in managing your stress. Remember, it's important to take care of yourself and seek support when needed. If you have any more questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask. Take care of yourself! Can you tell me more about the sleep reset program The Sleep Reset program focuses on helping individuals improve their sleep habits and overall sleep quality. Getting adequate and restful sleep is essential for maintaining good mental health and managing stress effectively. Through the Sleep Reset program, you can learn strategies and techniques to optimize your sleep environment, establish a relaxing bedtime routine, and address any sleep-related issues you may be experiencing.
